#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
pbx — one command to onboard, set up, and run the PBX trader lab locally.

Usage:
    ./pbx                  # interactive menu (onboard if needed)
    ./pbx status           # show lab status
    ./pbx wallet new       # generate a Solana keypair
    ./pbx wallet import    # use existing keypair (seed phrase or JSON)
    ./pbx wallet show      # show the bound wallet
    ./pbx achievements     # show unlocked + pending
    ./pbx refresh          # re-fetch backfill data
    ./pbx config           # reconfigure keys

This CLI is the offline side of the lab: discover top traders, decode
their strategies with the Python runners in lab/runners/, and backtest
the decoded rules on cached price data. It signs no transactions and
moves no funds. The separate live bot fleet (bots/) is opt-in — see
the README.

First run walks you through optional keys (Helius / PurpleAir), fetches
the on-chain backfill from the public PBX API, and saves config to
runtime/lab/ (Layer 3 — gitignored; override via STRATOS_LAB_HOME env
var). No keys are echoed. The decoder needs Helius or DATABASE_URL;
backtesting works against cached on-chain data.
"""
from __future__ import annotations

